1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:02,669
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

2
00:00:02,752 --> 00:00:05,213
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,591 --> 00:00:09,801
♪ <i>Fix this</i> ♪

4
00:00:09,884 --> 00:00:10,844
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

5
00:00:10,927 --> 00:00:12,804
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

6
00:00:12,887 --> 00:00:16,641
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i>
<i>In the tangle</i> ♪

7
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:18,977
[Atoy] <i>What happened here?</i>
<i>Why is she crying?</i>

8
00:00:19,060 --> 00:00:21,062
[Audrey] We need to find Janine's teacher,

9
00:00:21,146 --> 00:00:24,023
so I can talk to the one bullying her.

10
00:00:24,107 --> 00:00:25,817
[Gavin] <i>Isn't that just kids</i>
<i>quarreling, Auntie?</i>

11
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:27,610
I already told my mom about you!

12
00:00:27,694 --> 00:00:29,404
I told on you too.

13
00:00:29,487 --> 00:00:31,281
[Janine] <i>You'll be an orphan forever.</i>
<i>You're a loser!</i>

14
00:00:31,364 --> 00:00:32,782
[Atoy] Maybe it's better if you just

15
00:00:32,866 --> 00:00:35,535
bring me to her parents,
so we can settle this.

16
00:00:36,036 --> 00:00:37,120
- [indistinct]
- [Audrey] <i>Janine?</i>

17
00:00:37,203 --> 00:00:38,455
[clamoring]

18
00:00:38,538 --> 00:00:39,456
[Atoy] Stop that, stop that.

19
00:00:39,539 --> 00:00:40,498
[Ibyang huffs]

20
00:00:40,582 --> 00:00:41,416
[Atoy] Stop that.

21
00:00:41,499 --> 00:00:43,793
[Atoy] <i>So, you're the mother</i>
<i>of the one bullying Ibyang.</i>

22
00:00:43,877 --> 00:00:46,171
She's the one bullying my child!

23
00:00:46,254 --> 00:00:47,881
That's not true!

24
00:00:47,964 --> 00:00:50,675
Ibyang calls him "master".

25
00:00:51,259 --> 00:00:52,927
Who is he really?

26
00:00:53,011 --> 00:00:53,928
[Audrey] <i>So, it's just Atoy.</i>

27
00:00:54,012 --> 00:00:56,264
[Atoy] <i>And you, where's Janine's father?</i>

28
00:00:56,765 --> 00:00:57,891
Is she my daughter?

29
00:00:57,974 --> 00:01:01,102
[Audrey] <i>Didn't it occur to you</i>
<i>that I met someone else besides you?</i>

30
00:01:01,686 --> 00:01:03,146
[Tonet] <i>Is that the mother</i>
<i>of Ibyang's bully?</i>

31
00:01:03,229 --> 00:01:05,940
In fairness, she really
does look like Mama Mary.

32
00:01:06,024 --> 00:01:08,193
[exclaiming and squealing]

33
00:01:08,276 --> 00:01:10,403
[Tonet] I really don't want to!

34
00:01:10,487 --> 00:01:11,946
[exclaiming and squealing]

35
00:01:12,030 --> 00:01:13,406
Oh, just one gondola left!

36
00:01:13,490 --> 00:01:14,908
[Janine gasps]

37
00:01:14,991 --> 00:01:16,159
Mommy, we were here first.

38
00:01:17,035 --> 00:01:19,162
We were ahead by a few steps!

39
00:01:19,245 --> 00:01:22,707
[Atoy] <i>Uh, fine. Let them go first.</i>

40
00:01:23,792 --> 00:01:26,503
PREVIOUSLY

41
00:01:26,586 --> 00:01:27,670
[music fades]

42
00:01:28,379 --> 00:01:29,464
[toy gun cocks]

43
00:01:30,799 --> 00:01:32,175
[lively chattering]

44
00:01:32,258 --> 00:01:33,968
Mommy, come on!

45
00:01:34,052 --> 00:01:37,430
Don't miss. I want the biggest teddy bear.

46
00:01:38,348 --> 00:01:40,725
- Trust your mommy.
- [girl] Mommy!

47
00:01:40,809 --> 00:01:42,143
- That's your last shot, ma'am.
- [girl, indistinct]

48
00:01:42,227 --> 00:01:44,354
Don't pressure me, sir.

49
00:01:47,273 --> 00:01:48,274
- [clicks]
- [man gasps]

50
00:01:48,983 --> 00:01:51,736
- [Audrey gasps]
- Wow, ma'am, are you mad at me?

51
00:01:51,820 --> 00:01:55,031
Um, so… sorry, sir! I'm really sorry.

52
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:56,908
Mommy, one more.

53
00:01:56,991 --> 00:02:00,411
We're not leaving until I get what I want!

54
00:02:00,495 --> 00:02:02,080
After sir's turn.

55
00:02:02,914 --> 00:02:04,082
Sir?

56
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:08,044
What do you need to hit
to win the biggest teddy bear?

57
00:02:08,128 --> 00:02:10,171
The three in a row, sir.

58
00:02:10,255 --> 00:02:12,966
Mm, sure win, Ibyang. Watch, Ibyang.

59
00:02:13,049 --> 00:02:15,301
[rousing music playing]

60
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:16,302
‪[gun clicks]

61
00:02:16,386 --> 00:02:17,220
Oh, hey!

62
00:02:17,303 --> 00:02:18,930
[soft rock music playing]

63
00:02:19,764 --> 00:02:20,890
[both exclaims]

64
00:02:20,974 --> 00:02:23,143
- [Tonet] Wow, amazing!
- Ibyang.

65
00:02:26,146 --> 00:02:27,147
[both shriek]

66
00:02:27,230 --> 00:02:28,606
[Tonet] Wow! Incredible!

67
00:02:28,690 --> 00:02:30,191
[applauds]

68
00:02:30,942 --> 00:02:32,902
You're awesome, Master!

69
00:02:32,986 --> 00:02:35,697
- Congrats, sir. You're a sharpshooter!
- [girl] That one. Let's go.

70
00:02:35,780 --> 00:02:38,241
Mommy, I want that too!

71
00:02:38,324 --> 00:02:39,450
[Ibyang] Thank you.

72
00:02:39,534 --> 00:02:41,286
[in English] Thank you!

73
00:02:41,369 --> 00:02:43,204
[attendant] Ma'am, there's still
one big teddy bear.

74
00:02:43,288 --> 00:02:44,330
Just try again.

75
00:02:45,206 --> 00:02:47,375
I'm not good at shooting.

76
00:02:47,876 --> 00:02:49,711
Can I just buy it?

77
00:02:49,794 --> 00:02:52,839
If you just buy it, it loses its value.

78
00:02:52,922 --> 00:02:55,258
Things are better when you
work hard for them.

79
00:02:56,759 --> 00:02:57,886
You're right.

80
00:02:58,386 --> 00:03:01,097
If you want, ma'am,
just pay Sir Sharpshooter.

81
00:03:01,180 --> 00:03:03,016
Then you'll get the jackpot
for your child.

82
00:03:03,099 --> 00:03:05,143
[sneaky music playing]

83
00:03:05,226 --> 00:03:06,769
- I'm busy.
- [in English] Never mind!

84
00:03:06,853 --> 00:03:10,106
Janine, I'll buy you something
more expensive.

85
00:03:10,815 --> 00:03:11,649
Something bigger!

86
00:03:12,609 --> 00:03:13,610
Let's go.

87
00:03:14,235 --> 00:03:15,153
[attendant] Congrats, sir.

88
00:03:15,236 --> 00:03:16,779
- You're really good!
- Thank you.

89
00:03:16,863 --> 00:03:17,947
- Do come back.
- Thank you!

90
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:20,700
[suave theme music playing]

91
00:03:20,783 --> 00:03:23,077
[motorcycle revving]

92
00:03:23,161 --> 00:03:24,037
[sewing machine whirring]

93
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:24,996
[scratches]

94
00:03:25,079 --> 00:03:26,581
[snipping]

95
00:03:26,664 --> 00:03:28,499
[sewing machine clacking]

96
00:03:30,001 --> 00:03:31,169
[gun cocks]

97
00:03:31,252 --> 00:03:32,712
[gunshots blasting]

98
00:03:32,795 --> 00:03:34,172
[gunshots blasting]

99
00:03:34,255 --> 00:03:35,590
[clicking]

100
00:03:35,673 --> 00:03:37,675
[snipping]

101
00:03:38,968 --> 00:03:40,553
[electronic blipping]

102
00:03:44,933 --> 00:03:46,643
[music fades]

103
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:52,440
Hello! I'm Audrey.

104
00:03:53,316 --> 00:03:54,400
I know you.

105
00:03:55,526 --> 00:03:59,405
Aren't you the mother
of the one bullying Ibyang?

106
00:04:00,907 --> 00:04:03,785
Sorry, are you stalking me and Atoy?

107
00:04:04,285 --> 00:04:06,829
- Or just Atoy?
- [scoffs, in English] Of course not!

108
00:04:06,913 --> 00:04:08,456
Why would I do that?

109
00:04:09,207 --> 00:04:11,459
I have no interest in your boyfriend.

110
00:04:13,795 --> 00:04:17,131
[playful music playing]

111
00:04:17,924 --> 00:04:19,425
It's better that we're clear about this.

112
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:23,137
I'm just waiting for Janine,
then we'll leave.

113
00:04:23,972 --> 00:04:26,808
[in English] Then you can have
the whole theme park for yourself.

114
00:04:28,518 --> 00:04:29,852
[in English] Okay.

115
00:04:29,936 --> 00:04:33,273
Well then, I'll go to Ibyang and…

116
00:04:34,232 --> 00:04:35,275
Atoy, my love.

117
00:04:35,358 --> 00:04:36,609
[giggles]

118
00:04:36,693 --> 00:04:39,153
[music continues]

119
00:04:39,237 --> 00:04:40,071
Oh.

120
00:04:40,154 --> 00:04:41,447
[inaudible]

121
00:04:46,327 --> 00:04:47,245
Oh, one more.

122
00:04:59,966 --> 00:05:01,259
- [quirky sting]
- [scoffs]

123
00:05:02,427 --> 00:05:04,846
You show-off.

124
00:05:04,929 --> 00:05:06,014
[music fades]

125
00:05:06,514 --> 00:05:07,515
‪[quirky sting]

126
00:05:07,598 --> 00:05:09,058
[Tonet] There, that's it.
You're handsome again.

127
00:05:10,018 --> 00:05:11,227
[Janine] Mommy.

128
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:12,562
Janine.

129
00:05:13,062 --> 00:05:15,023
Let's go home.

130
00:05:15,106 --> 00:05:16,149
I'm not enjoying it anymore.

131
00:05:16,733 --> 00:05:17,692
Uh…

132
00:05:17,775 --> 00:05:19,610
[sneaky music playing]

133
00:05:19,694 --> 00:05:20,611
[Audrey sighs]

134
00:05:23,197 --> 00:05:27,785
[sewing machine whirring]

135
00:05:32,874 --> 00:05:34,000
[Atoy] Oh?

136
00:05:36,169 --> 00:05:37,378
You're still awake?

137
00:05:37,462 --> 00:05:40,882
I just want to thank you again, Master.

138
00:05:41,507 --> 00:05:43,342
Because of you,

139
00:05:43,426 --> 00:05:46,429
I don't even have space to sleep
beside that huge teddy bear!

140
00:05:46,512 --> 00:05:49,724
- [chuckles]
- [gentle music playing]

141
00:05:49,807 --> 00:05:51,142
Oh my.

142
00:05:51,768 --> 00:05:53,603
I'm just happy you enjoyed it.

143
00:05:54,687 --> 00:05:58,399
Janine almost ruined your day, right?

144
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:00,568
[smirks]

145
00:06:01,319 --> 00:06:02,737
You know, Master,

146
00:06:03,404 --> 00:06:06,657
I always keep in mind what you taught me.

147
00:06:07,492 --> 00:06:12,538
A negative person is like a thread…

148
00:06:13,289 --> 00:06:15,374
just passing through the needle.

149
00:06:15,458 --> 00:06:16,542
[both] Shoosh!

150
00:06:16,626 --> 00:06:18,586
[sentimental music playing]

151
00:06:18,669 --> 00:06:19,670
[in English] Very good.

152
00:06:20,963 --> 00:06:22,131
Come here.

153
00:06:23,424 --> 00:06:24,383
[Atoy] Hmm.

154
00:06:24,467 --> 00:06:28,721
[optimistic music playing]

155
00:06:33,184 --> 00:06:34,227
‪[Atoy chuckles]

156
00:06:34,894 --> 00:06:36,270
The coffee tastes great.

157
00:06:36,354 --> 00:06:37,522
What did you put in it?

158
00:06:37,605 --> 00:06:38,815
- [Ibyang] Master.
- Oh?

159
00:06:38,898 --> 00:06:41,109
It's still better if you
chase after me too,

160
00:06:41,192 --> 00:06:45,613
so I'll really have a cool dad!

161
00:06:45,696 --> 00:06:50,034
[chuckles] Cool!

162
00:06:50,118 --> 00:06:52,203
[chuckles]

163
00:07:00,837 --> 00:07:02,130
[music fades]

164
00:07:02,213 --> 00:07:03,589
Let me repeat it.

165
00:07:03,673 --> 00:07:08,219
We will hold the annual
beauty pageant for the primary level.

166
00:07:09,095 --> 00:07:11,013
Grades 1 to 6 may join.

167
00:07:11,764 --> 00:07:13,433
[Janine] Now I can join!

168
00:07:13,516 --> 00:07:14,434
Yes, you should join

169
00:07:14,517 --> 00:07:16,102
- because you'll win.
- Oh!

170
00:07:16,185 --> 00:07:17,019
- It suits you.
- I'm sure.

171
00:07:17,603 --> 00:07:19,730
And for those who want to join,

172
00:07:19,814 --> 00:07:22,525
tell your adviser and sign up.

173
00:07:22,608 --> 00:07:24,652
There will be a short screening,

174
00:07:24,735 --> 00:07:27,488
so only one representative per grade.

175
00:07:27,572 --> 00:07:28,698
[Ibyang] Wow!

176
00:07:28,781 --> 00:07:30,408
There's something like this here.

177
00:07:30,491 --> 00:07:32,577
Like Miss Universe!

178
00:07:32,660 --> 00:07:33,536
Yes.

179
00:07:34,036 --> 00:07:36,539
But you don't need to force yourself.

180
00:07:37,123 --> 00:07:38,541
You're ugly anyway.

181
00:07:40,710 --> 00:07:42,545
- You're beautiful, right?
- [sneaky music playing]

182
00:07:42,628 --> 00:07:43,963
Of course.

183
00:07:44,755 --> 00:07:48,176
And I'm sure you don't have money
to buy a gown for the pageant.

184
00:07:48,259 --> 00:07:49,594
While my mother?

185
00:07:49,677 --> 00:07:50,595
She does!

186
00:07:51,929 --> 00:07:53,347
Well, good for you.

187
00:07:56,517 --> 00:07:58,561
I'm still talking to you.

188
00:07:59,395 --> 00:08:00,771
Oh, I'm sorry.

189
00:08:00,855 --> 00:08:03,024
You still got something to say?

190
00:08:03,107 --> 00:08:04,066
Well, what is it?

191
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:06,152
Don't you ever join the pageant,

192
00:08:06,235 --> 00:08:07,528
because you'll only embarrass yourself.

193
00:08:07,612 --> 00:08:09,447
I'll beat you!

194
00:08:09,530 --> 00:08:13,284
[heavy music playing]

195
00:08:14,785 --> 00:08:18,289
So, Ibyang will join the pageant?

196
00:08:18,372 --> 00:08:20,374
[shrieks] Oh, very good! That's exciting!

197
00:08:20,458 --> 00:08:22,376
So, Janine will finally be embarrassed!

198
00:08:22,919 --> 00:08:24,629
Well, that's the thing.

199
00:08:24,712 --> 00:08:27,215
But she's worried about her gown.

200
00:08:27,298 --> 00:08:28,883
Is that a problem? Then let's--

201
00:08:28,966 --> 00:08:30,676
- Let's rent one!
- Rent?

202
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:32,845
Yes, let's just borrow one. It's cheaper.

203
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:33,804
No way!

204
00:08:33,888 --> 00:08:37,058
She doesn't want extra expenses.

205
00:08:37,141 --> 00:08:38,434
[Atoy] A gown, you say?

206
00:08:38,518 --> 00:08:40,520
I'll take care of Ibyang's gown.

207
00:08:40,603 --> 00:08:42,897
What else are our sewing machines
and fabrics for?

208
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:47,902
[sneaky music playing]

209
00:08:47,985 --> 00:08:49,320
Oh, okay, okay!

210
00:08:49,403 --> 00:08:51,280
Then I'll handle her makeup!

211
00:08:51,364 --> 00:08:53,199
And I'll teach her how to walk the runway.

212
00:08:53,282 --> 00:08:54,283
Like this, oh. [titters]

213
00:08:54,367 --> 00:08:56,619
Wait. Okay. Three, two, one!

214
00:08:56,702 --> 00:08:58,037
[in English] Contestant number 1!

215
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:01,624
[playful music playing]

216
00:09:01,707 --> 00:09:03,000
[Tonet] The "fierce" look. Like this.

217
00:09:03,584 --> 00:09:05,211
Then turn around like this.

218
00:09:05,294 --> 00:09:06,712
Uh…

219
00:09:06,796 --> 00:09:08,798
Do you even know how to sew a gown?

220
00:09:09,549 --> 00:09:10,383
No.

221
00:09:10,466 --> 00:09:11,509
‪[quirky sting]

222
00:09:11,592 --> 00:09:13,761
But I'll learn it for Ibyang.

223
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:16,013
[in English] Simple.

224
00:09:18,766 --> 00:09:19,976
Perfect!

225
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:23,229
Mommy, I need a beautiful gown.

226
00:09:23,854 --> 00:09:26,899
I need the most beautiful gown
in the pageant.

227
00:09:29,151 --> 00:09:33,239
"Mommy, <i>please,</i> I need a beautiful gown."

228
00:09:34,282 --> 00:09:35,324
Try saying that again.

229
00:09:36,075 --> 00:09:39,662
Please, I need a beautiful gown
for the pageant.

230
00:09:40,162 --> 00:09:41,080
All right, child.

231
00:09:42,123 --> 00:09:43,457
I'll make sure of that.

232
00:09:44,917 --> 00:09:46,127
That's a promise, okay?

233
00:09:46,210 --> 00:09:47,378
I really want to win.

234
00:09:48,045 --> 00:09:51,132
Yes, dear. You are going to win!

235
00:09:51,215 --> 00:09:52,633
We'll support you.

236
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:57,179
[somber music playing]

237
00:09:58,764 --> 00:09:59,599
‪[tense sting]

238
00:10:13,112 --> 00:10:14,405
[music fades]

239
00:10:17,408 --> 00:10:18,576
My child, I'm…

240
00:10:19,368 --> 00:10:20,703
[in English] I'm really, really sorry.

241
00:10:21,621 --> 00:10:22,872
[melancholic music playing]

242
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:26,000
I know I made such a big mistake with you.

243
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:29,337
[in English] I really hope you find
forgiveness in your heart.

244
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:32,548
[in English] I want to be a part of this.

245
00:10:34,175 --> 00:10:36,010
I want to make it up to you
and your daughter.

246
00:10:41,015 --> 00:10:43,059
[in English] Just give me some time, Dad.

247
00:10:44,477 --> 00:10:45,770
[in English] I'm trying.

248
00:10:45,853 --> 00:10:46,937
[Dmitri, in English] I know.

249
00:10:47,021 --> 00:10:47,897
[in English] It's just--

250
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:49,815
[in English] Yes. I know.

251
00:10:49,899 --> 00:10:51,150
You know, Dad…

252
00:10:53,235 --> 00:10:55,905
if you hadn't interfered
with my life on the island,

253
00:10:57,948 --> 00:10:59,492
my life could have been better.

254
00:11:03,287 --> 00:11:04,413
[in English] I'm sorry.

255
00:11:06,374 --> 00:11:10,002
This isn't how I imagined
your family life.

256
00:11:12,296 --> 00:11:14,882
I never wanted you to be a single mother.

257
00:11:16,967 --> 00:11:19,220
[in English] Ah, I'm really, really sorry.

258
00:11:19,804 --> 00:11:21,180
[in English] It is what it is.

259
00:11:23,849 --> 00:11:25,351
All I need to do is…

260
00:11:26,977 --> 00:11:28,646
whatever is best for me and my daughter.

261
00:11:38,614 --> 00:11:40,324
[music fades]

262
00:11:41,242 --> 00:11:43,411
[Mongki] Are you sure, Boss,
we're entering this industry?

263
00:11:43,994 --> 00:11:44,954
- You said it yourself.
- [dramatic sting]

264
00:11:45,037 --> 00:11:46,455
[in English] It's just business.

265
00:11:46,539 --> 00:11:48,374
I know, Boss, but…

266
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:50,292
It's simple.

267
00:11:50,376 --> 00:11:52,670
[in English] I move things
from point A to point B.

268
00:11:52,753 --> 00:11:53,587
[in English] That's it.

269
00:11:54,547 --> 00:11:55,965
There's no room for emotion here.

270
00:11:57,174 --> 00:11:59,343
All right. I'll handle it, Boss.

271
00:11:59,427 --> 00:12:02,096
We have people for that.
I'll take care of it.

272
00:12:03,889 --> 00:12:08,060
[tense music playing]

273
00:12:09,895 --> 00:12:10,938
[music fades]

274
00:12:11,897 --> 00:12:15,443
[in English] From Grade 4, Axle Eliseo!

275
00:12:18,654 --> 00:12:20,698
Our fourth contestant,

276
00:12:20,781 --> 00:12:23,325
from Grade 6, Anaiah Ong!

277
00:12:29,123 --> 00:12:32,501
Our fifth contestant, from Grade 2,

278
00:12:32,585 --> 00:12:33,919
Janine Ranoy!

279
00:12:38,632 --> 00:12:40,426
[in English] The sixth and last contestant

280
00:12:40,509 --> 00:12:43,888
for this year's annual beauty pageant,

281
00:12:43,971 --> 00:12:46,765
from Grade 1, Ivy Santos.

282
00:12:46,849 --> 00:12:51,854
[sneaky music playing]

283
00:12:52,771 --> 00:12:54,064
What are you doing here?

284
00:12:54,732 --> 00:12:56,650
You're Ivy Santos?

285
00:12:57,234 --> 00:13:00,112
You think Ibyang is my real name?

286
00:13:00,196 --> 00:13:02,740
Don't you use nicknames?

287
00:13:04,366 --> 00:13:07,411
[scoffs] Didn't I tell you
not to join the pageant?

288
00:13:08,913 --> 00:13:09,914
Yes.

289
00:13:09,997 --> 00:13:11,207
But why would I obey you?

290
00:13:11,957 --> 00:13:13,375
Are you my mother?

291
00:13:15,085 --> 00:13:17,213
You better watch out, Ibyang!

292
00:13:17,796 --> 00:13:18,964
You too.

293
00:13:25,137 --> 00:13:26,972
‪[machine whirring]

294
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:38,651
Hey!

295
00:13:39,151 --> 00:13:41,195
- Atoy! That looks beautiful!
- [chuckles]

296
00:13:41,695 --> 00:13:43,030
Is this good enough, Godmother?

297
00:13:43,113 --> 00:13:45,699
Is this good enough for my first gown?

298
00:13:45,783 --> 00:13:47,409
- [Cita] Wow!
- [chuckles]

299
00:13:48,619 --> 00:13:49,620
But wait.

300
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:52,373
What's this that Tonet told me?

301
00:13:52,456 --> 00:13:54,583
That woman at the theme park,

302
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:56,919
the mother of the one who bullied Ibyang?

303
00:13:57,545 --> 00:13:58,504
[Atoy] Ah. [scoffs]

304
00:13:59,964 --> 00:14:01,465
Do you remember, Godmother,

305
00:14:01,549 --> 00:14:03,467
the woman I told you about,

306
00:14:03,551 --> 00:14:04,969
the one I met on the island?

307
00:14:05,052 --> 00:14:07,346
- [pensive music playing]
- [inaudible]

308
00:14:07,429 --> 00:14:08,389
[gasps]

309
00:14:08,472 --> 00:14:09,807
The one you had a fling with?!

310
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:11,475
The one you met at the hospital,

311
00:14:11,559 --> 00:14:13,894
and now you met again at the theme park?

312
00:14:14,728 --> 00:14:16,355
Yes. That's her.

313
00:14:17,565 --> 00:14:20,192
Wow! What a coincidence.

314
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:22,236
It's like you're meant to be!

315
00:14:22,319 --> 00:14:23,404
[scoffs]

316
00:14:23,487 --> 00:14:24,572
Not really.

317
00:14:25,489 --> 00:14:27,366
She moved on quickly.

318
00:14:27,449 --> 00:14:30,160
[Cita] Hmm, from the tone of your voice,

319
00:14:30,244 --> 00:14:32,663
it sounds like you regret it.

320
00:14:32,746 --> 00:14:34,915
Do you want to reconcile with her?

321
00:14:35,499 --> 00:14:36,417
What for?

322
00:14:37,126 --> 00:14:38,419
Especially since she has a child already.

323
00:14:42,006 --> 00:14:43,591
[Emerson] Wait, wait, wait.
What did she say again?

324
00:14:43,674 --> 00:14:44,925
Hold on. Repeat that.

325
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:48,929
Atoy's ex is Mama Mary?

326
00:14:49,513 --> 00:14:52,057
Fool! She just looks like Mama Mary!

327
00:14:52,141 --> 00:14:53,684
- Clean your ears!
- [Emerson] Ah!

328
00:14:53,767 --> 00:14:56,770
- [Emerson] Hmm.
- And she wasn't his girlfriend!

329
00:14:56,854 --> 00:14:59,648
She was just a fling. That's different.

330
00:14:59,732 --> 00:15:01,025
- [Karla scoffs]
- "Fling"!

331
00:15:01,108 --> 00:15:02,234
That's the same thing.

332
00:15:03,527 --> 00:15:04,653
He only says that because

333
00:15:04,737 --> 00:15:07,072
maybe he doesn't want
to admit he was hurt.

334
00:15:07,865 --> 00:15:10,910
But that means it was
a serious relationship, right?

335
00:15:10,993 --> 00:15:11,827
Brother Kurt, right?

336
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:13,704
I agree with Emerson.

337
00:15:13,787 --> 00:15:15,414
Because Atoy, it's like…

338
00:15:15,497 --> 00:15:17,791
[in English] He loves
with his whole heart, right?

339
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:20,461
Actually, I didn't expect that.

340
00:15:20,544 --> 00:15:21,837
And you know what?

341
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:24,298
She's the mother of the one
who bullied Ibyang.

342
00:15:24,381 --> 00:15:26,050
- [Ame and Karla] Hmm.
- [Emerson] Hmm!

343
00:15:26,759 --> 00:15:29,345
So? How was it? Was it worth it?

344
00:15:29,887 --> 00:15:32,640
[in Visayan] Don't ask questions
like that, brother!

345
00:15:32,723 --> 00:15:35,059
Hmm, was that bad? I'm just curious.

346
00:15:36,268 --> 00:15:37,269
[Emerson] Hmm?

347
00:15:38,979 --> 00:15:40,689
Hmm, you have a point.

348
00:15:40,773 --> 00:15:44,151
Actually, you do have a point.

349
00:15:44,234 --> 00:15:47,112
It looks like Atoy really took
that woman seriously, right?

350
00:15:47,655 --> 00:15:49,073
And Atoy still looks

351
00:15:49,156 --> 00:15:50,866
really brokenhearted.

352
00:15:52,493 --> 00:15:54,203
When I was growing up,

353
00:15:54,286 --> 00:15:56,830
Mom used to say Brother Atoy had dates.

354
00:15:57,831 --> 00:15:59,333
But he never introduced anyone.

355
00:16:00,376 --> 00:16:02,002
It's like he never got serious.

356
00:16:03,295 --> 00:16:05,965
But I never imagined he could
be brokenhearted too.

357
00:16:06,048 --> 00:16:07,383
You know, here's the thing…

358
00:16:08,258 --> 00:16:10,052
In our world of handsome men…

359
00:16:10,135 --> 00:16:11,595
- [sneaky music playing]
- [all chuckle]

360
00:16:11,679 --> 00:16:13,555
It's just not obvious
because of our face card,

361
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:16,016
but we also feel
those kinds of things deeply.

362
00:16:16,100 --> 00:16:16,934
It hurts.

363
00:16:17,601 --> 00:16:19,937
- Get a check-up later, brother, okay?
- [Karla chuckles]

364
00:16:20,020 --> 00:16:20,854
It's something else.

365
00:16:20,938 --> 00:16:23,440
You know, I'll take care of Atoy's heart.

366
00:16:23,524 --> 00:16:26,694
Mm-mmm. I'll heal the wound.

367
00:16:27,361 --> 00:16:28,821
Mm, hm-hmm!

368
00:16:28,904 --> 00:16:31,490
[in Visayan] Just take care, Tonet, okay?
Just take care.

369
00:16:31,573 --> 00:16:34,034
Careful, you might end up
brokenhearted yourself.

370
00:16:39,206 --> 00:16:41,083
[Janine] Hey, little miss no-parents!

371
00:16:42,459 --> 00:16:44,712
It's still early,
and you're being negative.

372
00:16:44,795 --> 00:16:47,214
That's why you look old.

373
00:16:47,923 --> 00:16:50,217
- How dare you join the beauty pageant?
- [sneaky music playing]

374
00:16:50,718 --> 00:16:53,512
You're poor! And you can't
even buy a gown!

375
00:16:53,595 --> 00:16:55,305
Whatever!

376
00:16:55,389 --> 00:16:57,850
I have a tailor at home.

377
00:16:57,933 --> 00:17:00,394
He can make me ten gowns!

378
00:17:00,477 --> 00:17:02,021
"Ten gowns".

379
00:17:02,104 --> 00:17:03,522
But they'll still look cheap!

380
00:17:03,605 --> 00:17:05,190
That's why you still look ugly!

381
00:17:08,360 --> 00:17:10,946
Oh, here's five pesos!

382
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:13,574
Go buy yourself some good manners

383
00:17:13,657 --> 00:17:15,242
at the store, so you can win.

384
00:17:16,827 --> 00:17:20,456
Oh, Janine, Ibyang,
are you fighting again?

385
00:17:20,539 --> 00:17:22,249
Uh, no, Teacher.

386
00:17:22,332 --> 00:17:24,251
We're just talking. Right?

387
00:17:24,334 --> 00:17:26,086
Is that true, Ibyang?

388
00:17:26,670 --> 00:17:28,505
Talking with insults included!

389
00:17:28,589 --> 00:17:31,133
You really are a joker, huh!

390
00:17:31,216 --> 00:17:32,593
[teacher] You two.

391
00:17:32,676 --> 00:17:34,803
[in English] Please try
to be nice to each other.

392
00:17:35,387 --> 00:17:40,601
Anyway, tell your parents there's an
orientation tomorrow for the contestants,

393
00:17:40,684 --> 00:17:44,146
and the parents
are required to attend, okay?

394
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:46,607
- All right.
- [in English] Yes.

395
00:17:51,862 --> 00:17:53,030
[music fades]

396
00:17:53,614 --> 00:17:55,491
Atoy, Ibyang wants to remind you

397
00:17:55,574 --> 00:17:57,117
that tomorrow is their orientation.

398
00:17:57,826 --> 00:18:00,287
She'll go, and I'll go too.

399
00:18:00,370 --> 00:18:02,289
Yes, I'll go.

400
00:18:02,372 --> 00:18:03,373
You're so persistent.

401
00:18:03,457 --> 00:18:07,878
Oh, and she mentioned
that Janine's mother,

402
00:18:08,504 --> 00:18:09,838
Aunt Audrey, will also be there.

403
00:18:12,007 --> 00:18:12,966
- [rousing music playing]
- Ouch.

404
00:18:13,050 --> 00:18:14,593
[gasps] Atoy!

405
00:18:14,676 --> 00:18:15,511
Are you okay?

406
00:18:15,594 --> 00:18:16,887
- Is it an ouchy?
- [stammers]

407
00:18:16,970 --> 00:18:17,971
- I'm fine, fine, fine.
- Oh!

408
00:18:18,055 --> 00:18:20,182
"Ouchy"? What is this? Kindergarten?

409
00:18:20,265 --> 00:18:24,019
[Karla] Brother, you don't usually
get pricked by a needle.

410
00:18:24,103 --> 00:18:26,814
They just mentioned
Aunt Audrey would be there,

411
00:18:26,897 --> 00:18:27,856
and you got distracted.

412
00:18:29,108 --> 00:18:30,609
Audrey has an impact, huh!

413
00:18:30,692 --> 00:18:33,112
Psst, hey! Karla, stop it.

414
00:18:33,195 --> 00:18:34,780
What do you mean, "impact"?

415
00:18:34,863 --> 00:18:37,282
Fine, tell us the story then.

416
00:18:37,366 --> 00:18:38,784
Who broke up the relationship?

417
00:18:38,867 --> 00:18:41,120
[sneaky music playing]

418
00:18:41,203 --> 00:18:43,956
I still have work to finish.
Go on. Get out of here.

419
00:18:44,039 --> 00:18:46,166
You're talking nonsense.
You really are something, Karla!

420
00:18:47,167 --> 00:18:48,252
- I agree, Karla!
- [Karla chuckles]

421
00:18:48,335 --> 00:18:49,837
Ah, stop messing around!

422
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:51,463
[soft rock music playing]

423
00:18:51,547 --> 00:18:53,924
[Ame] Atoy, come on!
We just want to hear the story!

424
00:18:54,007 --> 00:18:55,384
You're so grumpy.

425
00:18:55,467 --> 00:18:56,510
Give me some tissue…

426
00:18:56,593 --> 00:19:02,099
Maybe Audrey broke up with you
because you're too grumpy.

427
00:19:04,643 --> 00:19:05,477
‪[machine whirring]

428
00:19:08,939 --> 00:19:10,732
[in English] Good morning, early birds!

429
00:19:10,816 --> 00:19:12,818
Let's wait for the other parents.

430
00:19:12,901 --> 00:19:14,570
Ten minutes, then we'll start.

431
00:19:18,991 --> 00:19:20,492
Is your ex here yet, Atoy?

432
00:19:21,827 --> 00:19:22,995
How would I know?

433
00:19:23,829 --> 00:19:29,001
[indistinct chattering]

434
00:19:30,294 --> 00:19:34,882
[sneaky music playing]

435
00:19:36,008 --> 00:19:37,509
‪[door squeaks]

436
00:19:37,593 --> 00:19:38,427
[door clicks shut]

437
00:19:40,596 --> 00:19:41,680
‪[indistinct chattering]

438
00:19:52,649 --> 00:19:55,736
[music fades]

439
00:19:59,031 --> 00:20:01,658
[quirky stinging]

440
00:20:01,742 --> 00:20:02,951
‪[sneaky music playing]

441
00:20:07,497 --> 00:20:09,833
[in Visayan] Let's make your ex jealous.

442
00:20:10,459 --> 00:20:11,501
Huh?

443
00:20:11,585 --> 00:20:13,462
Eh, I said you smell nice. [sniffs]

444
00:20:13,545 --> 00:20:15,088
Hmm, so good!

445
00:20:16,048 --> 00:20:16,882
‪[Atoy scoffs]

446
00:20:17,382 --> 00:20:19,551
[teacher, in English]
All right, everyone! Good morning!

447
00:20:19,635 --> 00:20:21,261
[in English] My name is Mrs. Trinidad.

448
00:20:21,845 --> 00:20:24,932
Today, I will discuss everything
you need to know

449
00:20:25,015 --> 00:20:27,392
about your child's beauty pageant.

450
00:20:39,446 --> 00:20:41,031
[music fades]

451
00:20:41,782 --> 00:20:47,913
- [balls bouncing]
- [indistinct chattering, cheers]

452
00:20:52,584 --> 00:20:53,460
[Gavin] Karla.

453
00:20:54,419 --> 00:20:55,337
Gavin!

454
00:20:57,172 --> 00:20:58,590
You're playing basketball here alone?

455
00:20:59,258 --> 00:21:00,133
I don't like staying at the house.

456
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:03,303
And you? Are you gonna play?

457
00:21:04,221 --> 00:21:06,223
Actually, I came from the barangay.

458
00:21:06,306 --> 00:21:09,017
I was hoping Cathy had an outreach today.

459
00:21:10,018 --> 00:21:10,852
Turns out she didn't.

460
00:21:12,062 --> 00:21:14,273
Why? What were you planning to do there?

461
00:21:14,356 --> 00:21:16,566
Didn't I tell you I'd make it up to you?

462
00:21:17,651 --> 00:21:20,237
[in English] You know what?
I think I've figured it out.

463
00:21:20,320 --> 00:21:22,614
Figured what out? Life?

464
00:21:22,698 --> 00:21:24,199
‪[sentimental music playing]

465
00:21:24,283 --> 00:21:26,201
[in English] That's why
I'm so drawn to Cathy.

466
00:21:26,827 --> 00:21:29,746
Because I see in her
that even though she's a rich kid,

467
00:21:29,830 --> 00:21:31,498
she still manages to help others.

468
00:21:32,374 --> 00:21:34,418
[in English] And in a way,
she inspires me.

469
00:21:36,586 --> 00:21:38,505
Karla, not to impose,

470
00:21:38,588 --> 00:21:40,257
but didn't you say you'd make it up to me?

471
00:21:41,174 --> 00:21:42,759
Maybe you could talk to her.

472
00:21:44,261 --> 00:21:45,554
What would I say?

473
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:51,560
Maybe you could convince her
to go on a date with me.

474
00:21:58,191 --> 00:21:59,735
[music fades]

475
00:22:04,364 --> 00:22:05,449
[Audrey] Hi.

476
00:22:05,532 --> 00:22:06,491
[door clicks shut]

477
00:22:06,575 --> 00:22:09,953
I didn't get your name the last time.

478
00:22:12,122 --> 00:22:13,248
Tonet.

479
00:22:13,957 --> 00:22:14,833
Tonet.

480
00:22:17,753 --> 00:22:21,631
Uh, I hope you don't think
I'm stalking you and Atoy.

481
00:22:21,715 --> 00:22:23,717
Mmm? I don't think you are.

482
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:26,887
Both Ibyang and Janine
are joining the pageant, right?

483
00:22:26,970 --> 00:22:29,306
So, I get why you're here.

484
00:22:31,266 --> 00:22:32,100
[in English] Okay.

485
00:22:34,186 --> 00:22:36,313
[in English] I hope
you don't mind me asking, but… [sighs]

486
00:22:38,023 --> 00:22:41,318
- Where is Ibyang's mother?
- [dramatic sting]

487
00:22:41,401 --> 00:22:42,944
We're still looking for her.

488
00:22:45,072 --> 00:22:48,033
But for now, Atoy and I
are acting as her parents.

489
00:22:48,575 --> 00:22:50,368
[sneaky music playing]

490
00:22:50,452 --> 00:22:51,661
Ah.

491
00:22:52,204 --> 00:22:55,582
So, you and Atoy
have been together a long time.

492
00:22:55,665 --> 00:22:56,750
[Tonet smirks]

493
00:22:58,460 --> 00:23:00,837
[chuckles softly]
Ah, it's been years already.

494
00:23:02,964 --> 00:23:04,549
So, how did you and Atoy meet?

495
00:23:06,802 --> 00:23:08,678
That was a long time ago.

496
00:23:10,097 --> 00:23:10,931
[Tonet] Mmm…

497
00:23:11,014 --> 00:23:12,557
You're his ex, aren't you?

498
00:23:13,391 --> 00:23:16,144
- [unsettling music playing]
- Uh…

499
00:23:16,228 --> 00:23:17,229
You know, it's just weird.

500
00:23:17,312 --> 00:23:18,688
It's really weird,

501
00:23:18,772 --> 00:23:20,899
because he never told me about you.

502
00:23:20,982 --> 00:23:23,777
Not even one time! [titters]

503
00:23:23,860 --> 00:23:25,779
I'll go now. I'll go ahead.

504
00:23:25,862 --> 00:23:27,656
[melancholic music playing]

505
00:23:34,913 --> 00:23:37,082
[in English] Three, two, one, go!

506
00:23:37,165 --> 00:23:39,084
[in English] One, two, three, four, down!

507
00:23:39,167 --> 00:23:41,419
[in English] One, two, three, four,
and then…

508
00:23:41,503 --> 00:23:43,338
[in English] One, two, three, four.
One more!

509
00:23:43,421 --> 00:23:46,133
[in English] One, two, three, four,
and down!

510
00:23:46,216 --> 00:23:47,801
[in English] And then, down.
And then, turn!

511
00:23:47,884 --> 00:23:49,219
And one more grind.

512
00:23:49,302 --> 00:23:50,512
[exclaims]

513
00:23:50,595 --> 00:23:51,721
[Ame] Amazing, Ibyang, wow!

514
00:23:51,805 --> 00:23:53,807
- Best in talent already!
- [Tonet] Yes!

515
00:23:53,890 --> 00:23:54,891
Hmm, fir--fir--

516
00:23:54,975 --> 00:23:57,978
First time we perfected your dance number.

517
00:23:58,061 --> 00:23:58,937
[exclaims]

518
00:23:59,020 --> 00:24:01,148
[Ame] So good! [chuckles]

519
00:24:01,731 --> 00:24:03,024
You're really, really good!

520
00:24:03,108 --> 00:24:07,237
[sewing machine whirring]

521
00:24:11,283 --> 00:24:12,576
Master…

522
00:24:13,493 --> 00:24:18,498
you'll both attend the pageant, right?

523
00:24:18,582 --> 00:24:19,666
[Tonet stammers]

524
00:24:19,749 --> 00:24:25,547
That's what being
your guardians is for, isn't it?

525
00:24:26,673 --> 00:24:29,384
[phone ringing]

526
00:24:29,467 --> 00:24:30,468
Wait, hold on.

527
00:24:30,552 --> 00:24:31,678
[phone rings]

528
00:24:31,761 --> 00:24:32,888
[suspicious music playing]

529
00:24:32,971 --> 00:24:34,014
Hey!

530
00:24:34,097 --> 00:24:36,141
- [Atoy] Hello, sir?
- Maybe that's work again!

531
00:24:36,224 --> 00:24:37,601
[Mercado] <i>How are you, Atoy?</i>

532
00:24:37,684 --> 00:24:40,228
I have an old VIP client.

533
00:24:40,312 --> 00:24:43,231
I said you could start right away.

534
00:24:43,899 --> 00:24:45,734
Let's meet tomorrow, so I can give you

535
00:24:45,817 --> 00:24:47,861
the details of what he's looking for.

536
00:24:48,445 --> 00:24:49,571
Tomorrow?

537
00:24:49,654 --> 00:24:51,156
[dramatic sting]

538
00:24:51,239 --> 00:24:53,533
Why do you sound hesitant?

539
00:24:57,537 --> 00:24:58,788
Uh…

540
00:24:59,789 --> 00:25:01,541
[music fades]

541
00:25:01,625 --> 00:25:04,878
Sir, this kid I'm taking care of
has an event at school tomorrow.

542
00:25:04,961 --> 00:25:06,254
I won't be available.

543
00:25:06,755 --> 00:25:11,218
[sentimental music playing]

544
00:25:11,301 --> 00:25:12,260
[in English] Yes, sir.

545
00:25:13,845 --> 00:25:15,555
I'm on it. I will make it up to you.

546
00:25:15,639 --> 00:25:17,807
I'll just take care of Ibyang first.

547
00:25:22,187 --> 00:25:23,438
‪[optimistic music playing]

548
00:25:23,521 --> 00:25:24,606
[Atoy] Okay.

549
00:25:27,567 --> 00:25:31,279
Yes, sir. Same meeting place. Yes.

550
00:25:33,156 --> 00:25:34,658
[music fades]

551
00:25:34,741 --> 00:25:37,244
- [electronic blipping]
- [tense music playing]

552
00:25:43,458 --> 00:25:44,334
UP NEXT

553
00:25:44,417 --> 00:25:46,711
Wow! Ibyang looks so beautiful!

554
00:25:46,795 --> 00:25:48,255
- [tense music playing]
- [teacher 2] She's right, Ibyang!

555
00:25:48,338 --> 00:25:50,340
I wasn't wrong to sign you up.

556
00:25:50,423 --> 00:25:52,092
Good morning!

557
00:25:52,175 --> 00:25:57,180
I'm excited to experience
everything for the first time!

558
00:25:57,264 --> 00:25:59,599
[audience cheering]

559
00:25:59,683 --> 00:26:00,642
[Janine] <i>Good thing you're here.</i>

560
00:26:00,725 --> 00:26:01,893
I need your help.

561
00:26:01,977 --> 00:26:04,980
[Janine] <i>I'll make sure Ibyang loses.</i>

562
00:26:05,063 --> 00:26:06,439
There's dirt on your face.

563
00:26:06,523 --> 00:26:08,191
Yes. Here, wipe it.

564
00:26:08,275 --> 00:26:09,776
[Janine] <i>That's embarrassing.</i>

565
00:26:09,859 --> 00:26:11,736
You're the one making a scene!

566
00:26:11,820 --> 00:26:13,947
So, you're saying I'm a liar?!

567
00:26:14,030 --> 00:26:16,324
I never said you're a liar!

568
00:26:16,408 --> 00:26:18,285
Looks like your child picked up
some of your attitude.

569
00:26:18,368 --> 00:26:19,411
What did you say?

570
00:26:19,494 --> 00:26:20,495
You have the same attitude.

571
00:26:20,578 --> 00:26:22,080
- What's your problem, huh?!
- Hey, hey, hey.

572
00:26:22,163 --> 00:26:23,248
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

573
00:26:23,331 --> 00:26:25,208
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

574
00:26:25,292 --> 00:26:28,962
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

575
00:26:29,045 --> 00:26:30,588
♪ <i>Fix this</i> ♪

576
00:26:30,672 --> 00:26:31,756
‪Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
